    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20281/150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Legation at Tangier</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-26T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 26, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. As previously reported in our 36, February 18<note n="28" xml:id="d397fn1"
                        >Not printed.</note> German subs are using Atlantic coastline of Spanish
                    Morocco and Tangier zone to elude pursuit by Allied planes and to lurk in
                    comparative safety in quiet waters preparatory to attacks on shipping entering
                    the Mediterranean.</p>
                <p>It is understood that Allied authorities are considering institution of a regular
                    air patrol of the Atlantic Spanish Morocco coast involving regular flights over
                    Spanish Morocco territorial waters. While previously Spanish shore batteries
                    apparently made no serious efforts to damage Allied planes approaching near the
                    coast more recently Allied Naval authorities have been intensely annoyed by the
                    more serious firing of such batteries against planes in active pursuit of
                    subs.</p>
                <p>I expect to see Orgaz<note n="29" xml:id="d397fn2">Gen. Luis Orgaz, High
                        Commissioner, Spanish Zone of Morocco.</note> in next few days when I
                    propose to bring this situation to his attention unless Department has some
                    objection. At such time I would state that Spanish authorities cannot reasonably
                    object on grounds of Spanish neutrality to pursuit by Allied planes of Axis subs
                    when these make use improperly of Spanish Morocco territorial waters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
